IN THE MATTER OF THE SUPREME COURT COMMITTEE ON PROFESSIONAL CONDUCT

S.W.2d

Supreme Court of ArkansasDelivered April 30, 1990 Per Curiam.

Dr. Wilma Diner of Little Rock, Arkansas, is appointed to the Supreme Court Committee on Professional Conduct for a term of four years, expiring May 1,1994. Dr. Diner is appointed as a member at-large replacing Ms. Nancy Wood of Little Rock, Arkansas, whose term has expired.

The Court expresses its gratitude to Ms. Wood for her dedicated and faithful service to the Committee.
